  "content": "# Install Corvia from source (or from release binary when available)\n# For now, build from source — replace with binary install for releases\n\n# Or build from the workspace's own repos:\n\n# This will be replaced with a release binary URL in production\nWORKDIR /workspace\n```\n\nNote: The Dockerfile will evolve. For the initial version, we can use a simpler approach that builds Corvia inside the container from the cloned repo. The exact Dockerfile depends on whether we have release binaries yet. For now, use a multi-stage build approach or install from the workspace's own clone.\n\n**Simplified initial Dockerfile:**\n\n```dockerfile\nFROM rust:1.85-bookworm\n\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y \\\n    curl git build-essential pkg-config libssl-dev cmake \\\n    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n",
